meless + process victory of the former. (In time + outside of time.) clusion: the DNA phylogenic memory packets con abolish profane time + transmute all reality into single mythic drama: the story told in \"Tears.\" This is the master archetype of our world; viz: isurpation + tyranny - the rightful deposed iounger king enters as an unknown powerless tranger - he is arrested by the usurper/ rant although innocent + brought before him they confront each other - in some way the nnocent stranger calls on his father the white haired woolbearded old the King t 1405 usurper is destroyed: the power positions of the young stranger + the usurper are reversed at the end. A ritual solemn murder is darkly hinted at. The usurper is cognate with Tears; the younger stranger The who is the rightful king) with joy. usurper has violated the lawful ways in \"Tears\" he has married his sister: the crime of incest which brings down doom on him in some way connected to the young stranger.) Intoxication is olved (mescalin); thus Dionysos is pointed to, but the Acts material points to Christ so the two are blended. This story may not be theological or even mythological but dealing with an actual primordial historic crisis in which the rightful king was deposed by a tyrant + his followers forced to emigrate, retaining knowledge of this + their civilization in the DNA memory packets timed to fire later on what is most sought for is the retrieval of the rightful king who in some way has seen \"eaten\" + \"drunk by his followers + can be reconstituted from their psychoi, as if they are genetic carriers of him (he is encoded in them in latent form - i.e. crypte morphosis). given the right signals, one of his followers turns into him + he is again alive. To make i detection more difficult the follower has no knowledge of this + is randomized into the is population of a given planet. autochthono 406 the slumbering, ready to be awakened, rightful king poses a threat to whatever autochthonic Empire 